  "texts": [
    "Artificial intelligence (AI) is continually transforming the way humans operate and has been integrated into various sectors such as agriculture, manufacturing, and advanced healthcare [25] [26] [27].",
    "For instance, since the introduction of AI for diagnosing and treating breast cancer, numerous academics, scientists, and researchers have conducted significant experiments utilizing various deep learning (DL) technologies for these purposes.",
    "[28] Despite this progress, a comprehensive evaluation of DL applications in breast cancer diagnosis and treatment from a bibliometric standpoint has been lacking.",
    "Specifically, existing literature has not adequately addressed six key areas such as:",
    "1) Trends in publishing and citations for AI research in breast cancer 2) Leading contributors in terms of authors, journals, organizations, and countries 3) Frequently used keywords and publication patterns in AI-related breast cancer research 4) The collaboration networks within this research domain 5) The thematic trends in AI applications for breast cancer diagnosis and treatment 6) Challenges and potential solutions for future research in this field This study aims to address the existing gap by examining the knowledge framework of artificial intelligence in breast cancer diagnosis and treatment through systematic bibliometric review methods."
  ],
